[134] user
do we have to pb artifact adapt after each new zip release?

[135] assistant
No — **not after every new ZIP release**. Use `pb artifact adopt` only when you need to reconcile local Promptbranch state with a ZIP that is **already present in Project Sources**, especially when it was uploaded manually. ## Rule ```text If release flow uploaded and verified the ZIP: → no adopt needed If you manually added the ZIP with pbsa / pb src add: → adopt is needed if you want local state/current artifact to point to it If the ZIP is only a code/tooling release for download/testing: → no adopt needed unless you also want it to become the current Project Source baseline ``` ## In your current case You had: ```text v0.0.190 = manually uploaded/adopted Project Source baseline v0.0.191 = tooling release that added adopt v0.0.192 = code/tooling release that improves artifact-current output ``` So after installing/testing `v0.0.192`, you have two choices. ### Option A — v0.0.192 is only a tooling/code release No adopt needed. You install it, test it, and maybe upload it later if you want, but `pb artifact current` may still show adopted source baseline `v0.0.190`. That is valid. ### Option B — v0.0.192 should become the current Project Source baseline Then you need either: ```bash pb artifact release . --sync-source --upload --print-confirm-command ``` followed by the confirmation command. Or, if you manually upload it with `pbsa`: ```bash pbsa chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.192.zip pb artifact adopt chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.192.zip \ --from-project-source \ --json ``` ## Best practice For normal releases, prefer the transactional path: ```bash pb artifact release . --sync-source --upload --print-confirm-command ``` That should package, upload, verify, and update state in one controlled workflow. Use `pb artifact adopt` as a **repair/reconcile tool**, not as the normal release path. ## Verdict ✅ Strengths — `adopt` solves manual-upload split-brain state. ⚠️ Weaknesses — using `adopt` after every release would blur normal release flow vs reconciliation. 🔍 Unknowns — whether you want `v0.0.192` to become Project Source baseline or only tooling release. 🧩 Next step — for `v0.0.192`, first install/test it; only adopt it if you intentionally want Project Sources and `pb artifact current` to move from `v0.0.190` to `v0.0.192`.

