[220] assistant
Yes — but automate it as a **guarded adopt transaction**, not as an unconditional side effect. ## Critical assessment `pb artifact adopt` mutates local Promptbranch baseline state: ```text .pb_profile/.promptbranch_state.json .pb_profile/promptbranch_artifacts.json ``` So it should **not** run automatically after every `--tests-only`, because `--tests-only` should remain validation-only. The safe automation is either: ```bash ./chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_release_control.sh --adopt-current ``` or: ```bash ./chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_release_control.sh --tests-only --adopt-if-green ``` The second one should adopt only if the full test report is green. ## Recommended v0.0.196 scope Add two explicit release-control modes: ```bash ./chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_release_control.sh --adopt-current ``` and: ```bash ./chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_release_control.sh --tests-only --adopt-if-green ``` ## Required behavior For `--adopt-current`, the script should: ```text 1. Resolve current VERSION, for example v0.0.195. 2. Build expected ZIP name: chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.195.zip 3. Verify local ZIP exists. 4. Run pb artifact verify on the ZIP. 5. Verify the ZIP exists in Project Sources. 6. Run: pb artifact adopt chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.195.zip \ --from-project-source \ --local-path ./chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.195.zip \ --json 7. Run pb artifact current --json. 8. Verify: runtime.version == state.source_version == state.artifact_version registry_current.version == VERSION ``` For `--tests-only --adopt-if-green`, the script should: ```text 1. Run full test/report. 2. Parse pb_test.full.<version>.report.json. 3. Continue only if: ok: true status: verified failure_count: 0 4. Then run the same adopt-current flow. ``` ## Guardrails It must fail closed if: ```text - full tests fail - report JSON is missing or invalid - local ZIP is missing - pb artifact verify fails - Project Sources does not contain the ZIP - Project Sources contains duplicate matching ZIP names - VERSION does not match ZIP filename - adopt result is not ok:true/status:adopted - final pb artifact current does not match expected version ``` ## What not to do Do **not** make plain `--tests-only` adopt automatically. This should stay true: ```text --tests-only = no baseline mutation ``` Adoption should require an explicit flag: ```text --adopt-current --adopt-if-green ``` ## Example target command After installing and uploading `v0.0.195`, you would run: ```bash ./chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_release_control.sh --tests-only --adopt-if-green ``` Expected final state: ```text runtime code: v0.0.195 artifact state: v0.0.195 Project Source ref: v0.0.195 registry current: v0.0.195 ``` ## Verdict ✅ Strengths — this removes the manual adopt step while preserving safety. ⚠️ Weaknesses — adoption is state mutation, so it must remain explicit. 🔍 Unknowns — whether you want the first version to support only `--adopt-current` or also `--tests-only --adopt-if-green`. 🧩 Next step — implement `v0.0.196` from `chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.195.zip` with guarded `--adopt-current` and optionally `--adopt-if-green`.

