Yes, it is **allowed by the script parser**, but the current implementation makes this combination unsafe/misleading: ```bash ./chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_release_control.sh \ --version v0.0.197 \ --run-tests \ --adopt-if-green ``` ## Critical assessment The script help says `--adopt-if-green` works with `--run-tests` or `--tests-only`. But the implementation does this: ```bash --adopt-if-green) adopt_if_green=1 adopt_current=1 ``` Then many normal release steps are skipped whenever `adopt_current=1`: ```bash if [[ ${tests_only} -eq 0 && ${adopt_current} -eq 0 ]]; then # import/download/compare/package/source-add/install... fi ``` So with: ```bash --run-tests --adopt-if-green ``` the script does **not** behave like: ```text full release workflow → run tests → adopt if green ``` It behaves more like: ```text run tests → adopt existing local ZIP if green ``` That means it expects this file to already exist in the **current working directory**: ```text ./chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.197.zip ``` and also expects it to already exist in Project Sources. ## Why pathnames can fail The script sets: ```bash repo_root="$(pwd)" local_zip="${repo_root}/${artifact_zip}" ``` So this command must be run from the repo root: ```bash /home/spikkie/git/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow ``` If you run it from another directory, it looks for the ZIP in the wrong place. It does **not** use `~/Downloads` for the adopt step. It expects: ```bash /home/spikkie/git/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.197.zip ``` ## Correct command for the current script For the workflow you already validated in `v0.0.196`, use: ```bash ./chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_release_control.sh \ --version v0.0.197 \ --tests-only \ --adopt-if-green ``` This means: ```text run full test/report only if green, adopt existing v0.0.197 ZIP ``` Requirements: ```text 1. You are in the repo root. 2. chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.197.zip exists in the repo root. 3. v0.0.197 is already uploaded/added to Project Sources. 4. v0.0.197 is already installed as the active runtime. ``` For adopt only: ```bash ./chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_release_control.sh \ --version v0.0.197 \ --adopt-current ``` ## My verdict on `--run-tests --adopt-if-green` It should be considered a **script design bug** in `v0.0.197`. Either the script should reject it: ```text --adopt-if-green is only valid with --tests-only ``` or it should support it properly: ```text full release workflow → package → source add/upload → install → run tests → adopt if green ``` Right now it claims to support `--run-tests --adopt-if-green`, but the `adopt_current=1` flag suppresses the full release path. ## Recommended v0.0.198 scope Patch release-control behavior: ```text 1. Make --tests-only --adopt-if-green the supported guarded-adopt path. 2. Reject --run-tests --adopt-if-green unless --tests-only is also set. 3. Improve error text: - local ZIP missing - Project Source missing - wrong working directory 4. Optionally add --local-zip PATH later, but not necessary yet. ``` ## Verdict ✅ Strengths — `--tests-only --adopt-if-green` works and is the safe intended path. ⚠️ Weaknesses — `--run-tests --adopt-if-green` is accepted but does not run the full release workflow because `adopt_current=1` disables those steps. 🔍 Unknowns — whether your `v0.0.197.zip` is already in the repo root and Project Sources. 🧩 Next step — use `--tests-only --adopt-if-green` for now, and fix the parser/guard in `v0.0.198`.

