[582] assistant
`v0.0.203` is **not accepted**. The release-control script correctly skipped adoption, so the current accepted baseline remains: ```text chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.202.zip ``` ## Critical assessment The failure is **not** in the new MVP-F2 artifact-download feature. The full suite reached the browser integration flow, and the failure happened in the existing Project Source overwrite check. The log shows: ```text test_suite.ok: false version: v0.0.203 browser.ok: false agent.ok: true ``` The MCP smoke was running the installed `0.0.203` code, so the package did install and start correctly. fileciteturn56file0 The failing condition is this: ```text IntegrationAssertionError: file source overwrite did not detect an existing source ``` The overwrite step itself returned `ok: true` and `persistence_verified: true`, but it reported: ```text already_exists: false added: true overwritten: false removed_existing: false ``` That violates the test expectation for the overwrite regression: the second upload of the same file should detect the existing source and classify the operation as overwrite/removal, not as a fresh add. fileciteturn56file0 ## What still passed These parts are green: ```text agent suite: true package hygiene: true version consistency: true rate-limit telemetry: clean ``` The report shows package hygiene verified with no bad entries and no wrapper folder, and version consistency verified across the `0.0.203` surfaces. fileciteturn55file2turn55file4 Rate-limit telemetry shows no modal, no 429, and no service rate-limit events. fileciteturn55file2 ## Interpretation This is a **browser/source overwrite regression or stale overwrite assertion**, not an artifact-download failure. The most likely causes are: ```text 1. The file source list had not fully settled before overwrite detection. 2. ChatGPT’s source row/card labeling changed again. 3. The overwrite detection logic failed to match the existing file source before upload. 4. The test assertion is now too strict if ChatGPT allows duplicate same-name sources instead of true overwrite behavior. ``` Given the MVP rules, I would **not accept v0.0.203** until this is resolved. The design says artifact download is supposed to land only in `.pb_profile/artifact_inbox/` and must not mutate accepted artifact state yet, but the full release still has to pass the existing browser/source regression suite. fileciteturn55file5 ## Recommended next step Build a **repair release**: ```text v0.0.203.1 ``` from: ```text chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.203.zip ``` Repair scope only: ```text - fix Project Source overwrite detection/settle logic, or - fix the overwrite test if the UI behavior changed and duplicate same-name upload is now expected - do not advance MVP-F scope - do not start v0.0.204 yet ``` Then validate: ```bash ./chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_release_control.sh \ --version v0.0.203.1 \ --tests-only \ --adopt-if-green \ --skip-docker-logs \ --prune-release-logs \ --release-log-keep 12 ``` ## Verdict ✅ Strengths — package/install/version hygiene passed; agent suite passed; rate-limit telemetry was clean. ⚠️ Weaknesses — browser source overwrite classification regressed: persisted upload was treated as fresh add, not overwrite. 🔍 Unknowns — whether this is a real product behavior change in ChatGPT Sources or a missing settle/matching wait in Promptbranch. 🧩 Next step — create `v0.0.203.1` as a repair release focused only on source-overwrite detection/test correctness; keep `v0.0.202` as the accepted baseline until the repair adopts successfully.

