[782] assistant
Built `chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.207.zip` from accepted baseline: ```text chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.206.zip ``` Release artifact: [chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.207.zip](sandbox:/mnt/data/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.207.zip) ## What changed Implemented **MVP-F6: protocol ask generation from current accepted baseline only**. Added protocol-aware ask generation: ```bash pb ask "continue next slice" \ --protocol \ --from-current-baseline \ --target-version v0.0.207 \ --print-request-json ``` Behavior: ```text - builds a promptbranch.ask.request envelope - reads current baseline from pb artifact current-equivalent state - includes current artifact/source refs and versions - includes target_version when supplied - can print the request envelope without sending the ask - when not using --print-request-json, wraps the prompt with BEGIN_PROMPTBRANCH_REQUEST_JSON / END_PROMPTBRANCH_REQUEST_JSON ``` Added helpers: ```text build_ask_request_envelope() render_protocol_ask_prompt() infer_next_normal_version() ``` ## Safety boundary This release does **not**: ```text download artifacts verify artifact-inbox ZIPs migrate candidates adopt artifacts mutate Project Sources advance artifact/source state package .pb_profile/ ``` ## Validation Passed from extracted ZIP: ```text py_compile OK 20 focused tests passed ZIP CRC/testzip OK artifact verify OK VERSION = v0.0.207 entry_count = 199 hygiene_violation_count = 0 wrapper_folder = false ``` Confirmed clean ZIP hygiene: ```text no .pb_profile/ no artifact_inbox/ no release_logs/ no *.log no nested ZIPs no pb_*.json audit files no task/session transcript files no .pytest_cache/ no __pycache__/ no *.pyc / *.pyo ``` I did **not** run the full live browser/agent suite. ## Next validation ```bash ./chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_release_control.sh \ --version v0.0.207 \ --tests-only \ --adopt-if-green \ --skip-docker-logs \ --prune-release-logs \ --release-log-keep 12 ``` ## Verdict ✅ Strengths — `pb ask` can now generate