Yes — that section matters. After the `v0.0.207` section, the document does **not** define `v0.0.208` yet. It defines: ```text # 13. Acceptance criteria # 14. Open questions ``` So before building `v0.0.208`, we should answer those open questions and update the plan. The document says MVP-F is complete only when the full chain works end-to-end: protocol ask, reply parse, artifact intake download/verify/migrate, guarded test/adopt, `pb artifact current`, and next protocol ask from the adopted baseline. fileciteturn65file0 ## My answers to the open questions ### 1. Direct download or browser-context download? Decision: ```text MVP: direct download only. Later: browser-context download. ``` For now, `pb artifact intake --download` should only download when the reply envelope contains a real `download.url`. If the URL is missing, expired, or UI-only, return: ```text artifact_download_url_missing ``` Do not guess from prose or try fragile UI download yet. ### 2. Store artifact URLs or re-resolve from answer IDs? Decision: ```text Store both, but treat URL as temporary. ``` Record: ```text request_id answer_id filename url_seen_at url sha256 after download ``` But the stable reference should be `answer_id`, not the URL. ChatGPT download URLs may expire. ### 3. Require reply envelope for all `pb ask`, or only `pb ask --protocol`? Decision: ```text Only require it for pb ask --protocol initially. ``` Plain `pb ask` should remain human/manual mode. Protocol mode should be strict and fail closed. ### 4. Reject prose without envelope or allow manual-only mode? Decision: ```text For --protocol: reject. For normal pb ask: allow manual-only. ``` So: ```text pb ask "..." → prose allowed pb ask "..." --protocol --json → envelope required ``` If protocol mode gets prose without envelope: ```text reply_schema_missing ``` ### 5. Multiple assistant answers for one user message? Decision: ```text Do not auto-select silently. ``` Default should parse the latest complete assistant answer only if exactly one protocol envelope is found. If multiple assistant answers or multiple envelopes exist: ```text reply_schema_ambiguous ``` Then require: ```bash pb task answer parse --answer-id <id> --json ``` ### 6. Infer `target_version`, or require operator supply? Decision: ```text Explicit first, inference optional later. ``` For now require: ```bash --target-version v0.0.208 ``` Later we can add: ```bash --infer-target-version ``` Reason: repair releases make inference risky. If current baseline is `v0.0.207.1`, the next normal target may be `v0.0.208`, but a repair target may be `v0.0.207.2`. ### 7. Repair releases in the protocol? Decision: ```text Make repair release explicit. ``` Protocol request should include: ```json { "release_type": "repair", "base_release": "v0.0.207", "target_version": "v0.0.207.1", "repair_reason": "validation failure / packaging defect / stale validator" } ``` And validation must enforce: ```text repair does not advance MVP scope repair includes repair note repair version is numeric suffix only future normal release builds from latest accepted repair ``` ### 8. Non-ZIP artifact support? Decision: ```text Later, yes. MVP-F stays ZIP-first. ``` For MVP, artifact intake should support only: ```text kind: zip role: candidate_release / repair_candidate ``` Later add: ```text kind: markdown_report kind: json_report kind: log_bundle kind: diagnostic_bundle ``` But these should not enter the release baseline path. ## What this means for `v0.0.208` The correct next step is **not yet implementation of a big ask/reply runner**. First, update the design plan with these decisions. Recommended next release: ```text v0.0.208 — MVP-F7 plan finalization and protocol decision hardening ``` Narrow scope: ```text - update promptbranch_ask_reply_protocol_design_and_mvp_plan.md - add explicit MVP-F7 section - add decisions for the 8 open questions - add schema fields for release_type, base_release, repair_reason, answer_id, url_seen_at - no artifact download changes - no migration changes - no adoption changes - no Project Source mutation changes ``` Then `v0.0.209` can implement: ```text MVP-F7 — Controlled Ask/Reply Transaction Runner ``` ## Verdict ✅ Strengths — the current plan correctly stops after `v0.0.207` and forces us to answer protocol edge cases before automating more. ⚠️ Weaknesses — `v0.0.208` is not defined yet, so building code immediately would be premature. 🔍 Unknowns — whether ChatGPT artifact URLs can be downloaded directly in all cases; MVP should fail closed when they cannot. 🧩 Next step — update the MVP plan first: define `MVP-F7` and lock the answers to the 8 open questions, then implement from `v0.0.207`.

