Built `chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.210.zip` from accepted baseline: ```text chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.209.zip ``` Release artifact: [chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.210.zip](sandbox:/mnt/data/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.210.zip) ## What changed Focused only on the protocol timeout failure you hit. The live failure showed the waiter saw no assistant response and timed out with `assistant_count: 0`, `assistant_text_length: 0`, and `submit_aria_label: Start Voice`; the service-side error was `ResponseTimeoutError` while waiting for parseable JSON. fileciteturn71file0 fileciteturn71file1 Implemented: ```text - pb ask --protocol --parse-reply no longer sends expect_json=true to the browser service. - Protocol replies are treated as envelope text first, then parsed by Promptbranch. - Added --protocol-timeout-seconds, default 120 seconds. - Service-backed protocol ask calls now apply the protocol timeout instead of waiting 900/600 seconds. - Protocol ask failures now emit structured JSON instead of empty stdout. - Failure JSON includes request_id, correlation_id, baseline, target_version, release_type, timeout, error_type, debug_artifacts, and explicit no-download/no-migration/no-adoption flags. - promptbranch_service_client ask timeout now respects the configured timeout instead of forcing >=900 seconds. ``` ## Safety boundary This release does **not**: ```text download artifacts verify artifact ZIP contents migrate candidates adopt artifacts mutate Project Sources advance artifact/source state package .pb_profile/ ``` ## Validation Passed: ```text 216 focused tests passed extracted ZIP focused tests passed py_compile OK ZIP CRC/testzip OK artifact verify OK VERSION = v0.0.210 entry_count = 200 hygiene_violation_count = 0 wrapper_folder = false/null ``` Clean ZIP hygiene confirmed: ```text no .pb_profile/ no debug_artifacts/ no release_logs/ no *.log no nested ZIPs no pb_*.json audit files no task/session transcript files no .pytest_cache/ no __pycache__/ no *.pyc / *.pyo ``` I did **not** run the full live browser/agent suite. ## Next validation ```bash ./chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_release_control.sh \ --version v0.0.210 \ --tests-only \ --adopt-if-green \ --skip-docker-logs \ --prune-release-logs \ --release-log-keep 12 ``` After adoption, retry the live protocol smoke with a shorter timeout: ```bash pb ask "Protocol smoke only. Return a valid promptbranch.ask.reply envelope with status no_artifact. Do not create a ZIP." \ --protocol \ --from-current-baseline \ --target-version v0.0.211 \ --parse-reply \ --protocol-timeout-seconds 120 \ --json \ | tee .pb_profile/release_logs/v0.0.210/pb_ask_protocol_smoke.v0.0.210.json ``` ## Verdict ✅ Strengths — fixes the exact timeout/empty-stdout failure mode and removes the raw-JSON wait from protocol mode. ⚠️ Weaknesses — it does not yet prove ChatGPT will follow the protocol envelope live. 🔍 Unknowns — whether the next live smoke will return a valid envelope or a structured `ok:false` failure. 🧩 Next step — validate/adopt `v0.0.210`, then rerun the protocol smoke.

