[925] assistant
`v0.0.210` did what it was supposed to do: the protocol smoke no longer hangs forever or writes an empty file. It now returns structured JSON failure output. But the smoke itself is **not green**. ## Result The output is: ```text ok: false status: reply_validation_failed detail: no BEGIN_PROMPTBRANCH_REPLY_JSON/END_PROMPTBRANCH_REPLY_JSON block found reply_validation_errors: - reply_schema_missing ``` The request baseline is correct: ```text current_baseline: chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.210.zip current_version: v0.0.210 target_version: v0.0.211 ``` So baseline continuity is working. fileciteturn72file0 ## Critical finding The parsed `ask_response.answer` is **stale**. It contains the previous assistant response about building `v0.0.210`, not a fresh answer to the protocol-smoke request. That means the next bug is probably: ```text pb ask --protocol --parse-reply is parsing the latest existing assistant answer, not reliably waiting for / selecting the assistant answer generated after the new request. ``` So this is not primarily a schema/prompt problem anymore. It is a **turn correlation / stale-answer detection problem**. ## What v0.0.210 fixed ✅ structured failure JSON instead of empty stdout ✅ bounded protocol timeout path ✅ baseline/request metadata preserved ✅ no download/migrate/adopt side effects ✅ fail-closed behavior ## What still fails ⚠️ `--parse-reply` can validate the wrong assistant answer ⚠️ no stale-answer guard ⚠️ no proof yet that a fresh ChatGPT answer preserves the protocol envelope ## Next release ```text v0.0.211 — protocol stale-answer detection and stricter envelope prompting ``` Narrow scope: ```text - record the pre-ask latest assistant/message id or turn index - after submit, require a newer assistant answer than the pre-ask marker - fail closed with stale_answer_detected if only old answers are visible - include selected answer_id / turn_index in JSON output - improve prompt text so protocol mode strongly requires BEGIN/END envelope - no artifact download - no migration - no adoption changes - no Project Source mutation ``` ## Immediate confirmation command Run this once to prove `v0.0.210` is truly current: ```bash pb artifact current --json | python3 -m json.tool ``` ## Verdict ✅ Strengths — `v0.0.210` fixed the automation-breaking empty-output/hang failure. ⚠️ Weaknesses — `--parse-reply` selected a stale assistant answer. 🔍 Unknowns — whether ChatGPT produced a later answer that the selector missed, or whether no new answer was generated. 🧩 Next step — build `v0.0.211` from `chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.210.zip` with protocol stale-answer detection and stricter envelope prompting only.

