Built `chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.211.zip` from accepted baseline: ```text chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.210.zip ``` Release artifact: [chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.211.zip](sandbox:/mnt/data/chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.211.zip) ## What changed Implemented **protocol stale-answer detection and stricter envelope prompting only**. Main changes: ```text - Captures a pre-ask task marker before pb ask --protocol --parse-reply. - Requires the parsed assistant answer to be newer than the pre-ask marker. - Also accepts a reply tied to the current request_id. - Fails closed with stale_answer_detected when only old answers are visible. - Fails closed with assistant_not_detected when the new request exists but has no assistant answer. - Adds selected_answer metadata: message_id, message_index, turn_index, answer_id. - Adds pre_ask_marker and post_ask_marker to protocol-run JSON. - Strengthens the protocol prompt: exactly one BEGIN/END reply envelope, no Markdown code fence, no previous-response summary. ``` ## Safety boundary No changes to: ```text artifact download artifact verification candidate migration artifact adoption Project Source mutation artifact/source current-state advancement ``` ## Validation Passed: ```text 208 focused tests passed on extracted ZIP py_compile OK ZIP CRC/testzip OK artifact verify OK VERSION = v0.0.211 entry_count = 200 hygiene_violation_count = 0 wrapper_folder = false/null ``` Clean ZIP hygiene confirmed: ```text no .pb_profile/ no debug_artifacts/ no release_logs/ no *.log no nested ZIPs no pb_*.json audit files no task/session transcript files no .pytest_cache/ no __pycache__/ no *.pyc / *.pyo ``` One note: unconstrained `pytest -q` still hits the existing duplicate-module collection issue around legacy `chatgpt_*` / `promptbranch_*` integration files. I validated the focused project test set instead. ## Next validation ```bash ./chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_release_control.sh \ --version v0.0.211 \ --tests-only \ --adopt-if-green \ --skip-docker-logs \ --prune-release-logs \ --release-log-keep 12 ``` Then retry: ```bash pb ask "Protocol smoke only. Return a valid promptbranch.ask.reply envelope with status no_artifact. Do not create a ZIP." \ --protocol \ --from-current-baseline \ --target-version v0.0.212 \ --parse-reply \ --protocol-timeout-seconds 120 \ --json \ | tee .pb_profile/release_logs/v0.0.211/pb_ask_protocol_smoke.v0.0.211.json ``` ## Verdict ✅ Strengths — stale latest-answer selection is now explicitly guarded. ⚠️ Weaknesses — live ChatGPT envelope compliance still needs proof after adoption. 🔍 Unknowns — whether the next smoke returns a valid envelope or `assistant_not_detected` / `stale_answer_detected`. 🧩 Next step — validate/adopt `v0.0.211`, then rerun the protocol smoke.

