[989] assistant
`v0.0.211` adopted cleanly, but the live protocol smoke is **still not green**. ## Critical assessment `v0.0.211` did improve the failure mode: it no longer silently parses the stale answer as if it were valid. It now fails closed with: ```text status: stale_answer_detected error: stale_answer_detected: no user message newer than the protocol ask pre-marker was found ``` The JSON also shows the stale answer it saw was still the previous assistant response about building `v0.0.211`, not a fresh reply to the protocol smoke. fileciteturn74file0 So the new guard works, but the underlying live issue remains: ```text pb ask submits or attempts to submit, but the post-ask task/message reader does not see a newer user turn. ``` ## What this means This is no longer mainly a parser problem. The next failure class is: ```text ask submission / task refresh / post-ask message discovery ``` Possible causes: ```text 1. The ask was not actually submitted. 2. The ask was submitted, but the task reader is using stale cached conversation data. 3. The new turn exists in the browser but is not visible through the backend/task extraction path yet. 4. The pre/post marker logic captures the same conversation snapshot because no forced refresh happened after ask. ``` ## Next release scope Recommended next release: ```text v0.0.212 — protocol ask fresh-turn verification and post-submit refresh ``` Narrow scope only: ```text - after protocol ask submit, force a task/message refresh before parsing - verify a newer user message exists after submit - return ask_submission_not_visible if no newer user turn appears - include submit evidence: before/after message counts, latest user ids, latest answer ids - optionally wait/poll for a newer user turn before waiting for assistant answer - do not download artifacts - do not migrate candidates - do not adopt - do not mutate Project Sources ``` ## Immediate debug command Run this after the failed smoke: ```bash pb task messages list --json \ | tee .pb_profile/release_logs/v0.0.211/pb_task_messages_after_protocol_smoke.v0.0.211.json ``` Then check whether your smoke prompt appears as a new user message: ```bash grep -n "Protocol smoke only" .pb_profile/release_logs/v0.0.211/pb_task_messages_after_protocol_smoke.v0.0.211.json ``` ## Verdict ✅ Strengths — `v0.0.211` correctly detects stale-answer reuse instead of accepting it. ⚠️ Weaknesses — the live ask path still does not prove that a fresh user turn is visible after submit. 🔍 Unknowns — whether the submit failed, the backend snapshot is stale, or the task reader needs forced refresh/polling. 🧩 Next step — build `v0.0.212` from `chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.211.zip` with fresh-turn verification and post-submit refresh only.

