ion_not_visible` as a fail-closed status when the protocol ask does not become visible after post-submit refresh/polling.\n- Added fresh-turn evidence to protocol-run JSON: before/after message counts, request-message visibility, attempts, and latest markers.\n- No artifact download, migration, adoption, Project Source mutation, or state advancement behavior changed.\n\n''' s=s.replace(marker, section+marker,1) p.write_text(s) p=Path('UPGRADING.md') s=p.read_text() if '## v0.0.212' not in s: marker='## v0.0.211' section='''## v0.0.212\n\n- `pb ask --protocol --parse-reply` now verifies that the submitted protocol ask is visible as a fresh user turn before parsing any assistant answer.\n- Failure now returns `ask_submission_not_visible` with fresh-turn evidence instead of falling through to stale-answer parsing.\n- New tuning options: `--protocol-fresh-turn-timeout-seconds` and `--protocol-fresh-turn-poll-seconds`.\n- Artifact intake/adoption behavior is unchanged.\n\n''' s=s.replace(marker, section+marker,1) p.write_text(s) PY python3 -m py_compile promptbranch_cli.py tests/test_promptbranch_cli.py tests/test_cli_parser.py tests/test_promptbranch_mcp.py

