`v0.0.214` improved the diagnosis. The failure is now **not** `service_read_timeout`. ## Critical assessment The run failed with: ```text status: ask_submission_not_visible ``` But now we have useful submit evidence: ```text submit_evidence.status: clicked_submit_button clicked: true button_visible: true button_enabled: true composer_cleared: true after_composer.text_length: 0 ``` So the browser automation **did click Send**, and the composer cleared afterward. That means `v0.0.214` successfully fixed the previous timeout-layer problem: the CLI got structured evidence back instead of losing everything to `ReadTimeout`. fileciteturn80file0 ## What still failed The new user turn was not detected: ```text dom_user_turn_evidence.visible: false before_count: 0 after_count: 0 count_delta: 0 request_id_found: false ``` And backend/task refresh also did not see a new message: ```text message_count_before: 93 message_count_after: 93 message_count_delta: 0 request_message_found: false fresh_user_turn_visible: false ``` The stale `ask_response.answer` is still the previous assistant answer about building `v0.0.214`, so the guard correctly refused to parse it. ## Important interpretation This is now a **submit visibility / transcript refresh problem**, not an ask protocol parser problem. The key suspicious detail is this: ```text before_user_turns.count: 0 ``` In an existing conversation with 93 messages, DOM probing found **zero** user turns even before submit. That suggests the DOM selectors for user turns are probably wrong or the visible conversation is virtualized in a way the current probes do not see. So the next fix should not assume “submit failed.” The evidence is more nuanced: ```text button clicked + composer cleared but no user bubble visible through current DOM probes and backend/task message count stayed stale ``` ## Next release scope Proceed with: ```text v0.0.215 — protocol ask submit visibility and transcript-refresh hardening ``` Narrow scope: ```text - improve DOM user-turn selectors / probes - capture generic conversation turn counts, not only user-specific selectors - detect whether ChatGPT uses a different message DOM structure - add a forced backend/task refresh path after submit - distinguish: - ask_clicked_composer_cleared_dom_selector_missed - ask_clicked_composer_cleared_backend_stale - ask_clicked_but_no_turn_materialized - include before/after DOM HTML/text snippets around conversation turns - no artifact download - no migration - no adoption - no Project Source mutation ``` ## Immediate debug command Run this to see if the message exists in backend/task output now: ```bash pb task messages list --json \ | tee .pb_profile/release_logs/v0.0.214/pb_task_messages_after_protocol_smoke.v0.0.214.json grep -n "req_20260514T085319452699Z\|Protocol smoke only" \ .pb_profile/release_logs/v0.0.214/pb_task_messages_after_protocol_smoke.v0.0.214.json ``` ## Verdict ✅ Strengths — `v0.0.214` fixed the timeout-layer issue and returned useful submit evidence. ⚠️ Weaknesses — the new turn is still not visible through DOM probes or backend task refresh. 🔍 Unknowns — whether the turn was truly not created, or the current selectors/backend refresh are stale/missing it. 🧩 Next step — build `v0.0.215` from `chatgpt_claudecode_workflow_v0.0.214.zip` with submit visibility and transcript-refresh hardening only.

